===============================================================================
Fusim - FUSion SIMulator
===============================================================================

Fusim is a program to simulate fusion genes from a reference genome. 

---------------------
Requirements
---------------------

- Java
- UCSC RefGene model
- Reference genome in fasta
- samtools (for indexing only)

---------------------
Setup
---------------------

1. Download UCSC RefGene models:

  $ wget -O refGene.txt.gz http://hgdownload.cse.ucsc.edu/goldenPath/hg19/database/refGene.txt
  $ gunzip refGene.txt.gz


2. Download genome reference from UCSC:

  $ wget ftp://hgdownload.cse.ucsc.edu/goldenPath/hg19/bigZips/chromFa.tar.gz

3. Extract and build one single fasta file:

  $ tar -xzf chromFa.tar.gz
  $ cat chr*.fa > hg19.fa

4. Index with samtools:

  $ samtools faidx hg19.fa


---------------------
Basic Usage
---------------------

$ java -jar fusim.jar 
usage: fusim
-b,--bam <arg>         Background BAM file
-g,--genemodel <arg>   Gene Model file
-h,--help              print usage info
-n,--fusions <arg>     Total number of fusions to generate
-o,--out <arg>         Output file
-r,--reference <arg>   Reference genome (fasta)
-t,--type <arg>        Format of output [fasta|txt]


- Generate a single Fusion gene using UCSC refGene.txt model:

  $ java -jar fusim.jar -g refGene.txt -n 1

- Generate 100 Fusion genes using UCSC refGene.txt model:

  $ java -jar fusim.jar -g refGene.txt -n 100

- Generate 10 Fusion genes using UCSC refGene.txt model and a background
  dataset (BAM file):

  $ java -jar fusim.jar -g refGene.txt -n 100 -b background-reads.bam

- Generate 10 Fusion genes and their sequences in FASTA format:

  $ java -jar fusim.jar -g refGene.txt -n 100 -t fasta -r hg19.fa

